    "_postman_id": "4747e269-1e21-461c-a931-3537ba815d33",
    "name": "Gear Up",
    "description": "# 🚀 GearUp Rental API\n\nGearUp is a Sports & Outdoor Equipment Rental Platform.\n\nThis API allows customers to rent equipment, providers to manage inventory, and administrators to oversee the platform.\n\n## 🔒 Authentication\n\nAuthentication uses JWT Bearer Token.\n\nAfter logging in, copy the access token and set\n\nAuthorization  \nBearer Token\n\n{{accessToken}}\n\n## Base URL\n\n#### Development\n\n[http://localhost:4](http://localhost:4000)[000](http://localhost:4000)\n\n#### Production\n\n[https://gearup-rental-api.vercel.app](https://your-domain.vercel.app/api)\n\n## 👤 Allowed Roles\n\nAdmin\n\nProvider\n\nCustomer\n\n## Response Format\n\n## 📤 Success Format\n\n{  \n\"success\": true,  \n\"statusCode\": 200,  \n\"message\": \"Success message\",  \n\"data\": {}  \n}\n\n## ❌ Error Format\n\n{  \n\"success\": false,  \n\"message\": \"Something went wrong\",  \n\"errorDetails\": {}  \n}\n\n## 📝 Status Flow\n\nOne section should explain the complete rental lifecycle.\n\nPLACED  \n│  \n▼  \nCONFIRMED  \n│  \n▼  \nPAID  \n│  \n▼  \nPICKED_UP  \n│  \n▼  \nRETURNED\n\nPLACED ─────────► CANCELLED\n\nCONFIRMED ──────► CANCELLED\n\n## 📝 Payment Flow\n\nCustomer  \n│  \n▼  \nCreate Rental  \n│  \n▼  \nRental Order Created  \n│  \n▼  \nSSLCommerz Session  \n│  \n▼  \npaymentUrl Returned  \n│  \n▼  \nCustomer Pays  \n│  \n▼  \nSSLCommerz Callback  \n│  \n▼  \nValidate Transaction  \n│  \n▼  \nPayment → PAID  \n│  \n▼  \nRental → PAID\n\n## ❌ Error Codes\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| 400 | Bad Request |\n| 401 | Unauthorized |\n| 403 | Forbidden |\n| 404 | Resource Not Found |\n| 409 | Conflict |\n| 500 | Internal Server Error |\n| 502 | Payment Gateway Error |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "54304563",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/54304563-4747e269-1e21-461c-a931-3537ba815d33?source=collection_link"
  },
